But Pattloch ’ s cases are different: on behalf of his clients, he claims that Chinese companies are officially given the right by the Trademark Office to use a designation that is already protected elsewhere.
The Chinese call this "Bang Mingpai", a passenger brand.
The word is based on "Bang Dakuan".
