What symptoms indicate venereal disease?
Infectious diseases can cause ulcers in the genital area, problems with urination, discharge, abdominal pain as well as vesicles or warts.
However, they often do not cause pain or other symptoms and therefore remain unnoticed.
How to protect yourself?
Condoms can reduce the risk of infection, but do not provide 100% protection.
In part, pathogens of sexually transmitted diseases can also be passed on through lubricating infections and close physical contact.
