About 400 carriers load the baskets with sulphur on their shoulders at the crater bottom.
Despite its large profits, the mining company has not mechanized sulphur mining to save costs, and does not provide any equipment to carriers working on their own account and paying for weight.
They also do not receive a share of the 30,000 rupees (2.5 euros) per camera, which the guardians of this nature park together with the entrance fee of 15,000 rupees (1.2 euros) demand from the tourists who come to take pictures of the volcano and the human carrier.
